===Definitions===
{{head|zh|hanzi}}

# to [[resent]]; to [[hate]]
#: {{zh-co|可恨|abominable}}
#: {{zh-x|我 恨 死 你 了！|I hate you to death!}}
# to [[regret]]; to [[pity]]
#: {{zh-co|恨不得|to wish that one could ("'''to regret''' that one may not")}}
#: {{zh-co|恨鐵不成鋼|'''to pity''' someone's lack of improvement}}
## {{lb|zh|chiefly|literary}} to [[pine]]; to [[long]] for; to [[miss]]; to [[suffer]] from [[intense]] [[desire]]
##* {{zh-x|輟 耕 之 壟 上，悵恨 久之，曰：「苟 富貴，無 相{xiāng}-忘。」|Taking a break from the work, he went up a raised slope by the fields. Full of care and '''discontent''' with himself for quite a while, he burst out, "Lest we forget one another when greatness is achieved!"|ref=Shiji}}
##* {{zh-x|解釋 春風 無限 恨|Vanquished are the endless '''longings of love'''|CL|ref={{circa2|the early 740s|short=yes}}, {{w|Li Bai}} ({{lw|zh|李白}}), ''Qing Ping Diao'' ({{lang|zh|《[[s:zh:清平調|清平調]]》}}). English translation by Shigeyoshi Obata ({{lang|ja|小畑薫良}}), 1922.}}
# [[hatred]]; [[dislike]]
#: {{zh-co|抱恨|to be bitterly regretful}}
#: {{zh-co|懷恨在心|to harbour hatred; to entertain hateful thoughts}}
#* {{zh-x|世上 決 沒有 無緣無故 的 愛，也 沒有 無緣無故 的 恨。|There is absolutely no such thing in the world as love or hatred with out reason or cause.|ref=MaoYanan}}
# {{lb|zh|Cantonese}} to be [[eager]] for something

